From: Daniel Gomez <da.gomez@samsung.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Dec 2025 04:49:37 +0100
Subject: dm: replace -EEXIST with -EBUSY
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc1
Git-commit: b13ef361d47f09b7aecd18e0383ecc83ff61057e
References: git-fixes

The -EEXIST error code is reserved by the module loading infrastructure
to indicate that a module is already loaded. When a module's init
function returns -EEXIST, userspace tools like kmod interpret this as
"module already loaded" and treat the operation as successful, returning
0 to the user even though the module initialization actually failed.

This follows the precedent set by commit 54416fd76770 ("netfilter:
conntrack: helper: Replace -EEXIST by -EBUSY") which fixed the same
issue in nf_conntrack_helper_register().

Affected modules:
  * dm_cache dm_clone dm_integrity dm_mirror dm_multipath dm_pcache
  * dm_vdo dm-ps-round-robin dm_historical_service_time dm_io_affinity
  * dm_queue_length dm_service_time dm_snapshot

Signed-off-by: Daniel Gomez <da.gomez@samsung.com>
Signed-off-by: Mikulas Patocka <mpatocka@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Martin Wilck <mwilck@suse.com>
---
 drivers/md/dm-exception-store.c |    2 +-
 drivers/md/dm-log.c             |    2 +-
 drivers/md/dm-path-selector.c   |    2 +-
 drivers/md/dm-target.c          |    2 +-
 4 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/md/dm-exception-store.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-exception-store.c
@@ -116,7 +116,7 @@ int dm_exception_store_type_register(str
 	if (!__find_exception_store_type(type->name))
 		list_add(&type->list, &_exception_store_types);
 	else
-		r = -EEXIST;
+		r = -EBUSY;
 	spin_unlock(&_lock);
 
 	return r;
--- a/drivers/md/dm-log.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-log.c
@@ -121,7 +121,7 @@ int dm_dirty_log_type_register(struct dm
 	if (!__find_dirty_log_type(type->name))
 		list_add(&type->list, &_log_types);
 	else
-		r = -EEXIST;
+		r = -EBUSY;
 	spin_unlock(&_lock);
 
 	return r;
--- a/drivers/md/dm-path-selector.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-path-selector.c
@@ -107,7 +107,7 @@ int dm_register_path_selector(struct pat
 
 	if (__find_path_selector_type(pst->name)) {
 		kfree(psi);
-		r = -EEXIST;
+		r = -EBUSY;
 	} else
 		list_add(&psi->list, &_path_selectors);
 
--- a/drivers/md/dm-target.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-target.c
@@ -88,7 +88,7 @@ int dm_register_target(struct target_typ
 	if (__find_target_type(tt->name)) {
 		DMERR("%s: '%s' target already registered",
 		      __func__, tt->name);
-		rv = -EEXIST;
+		rv = -EBUSY;
 	} else {
 		list_add(&tt->list, &_targets);
 	}
